The paper deals with the complexity of finding succinct solutions to PSPACE-complete problems, which are typically studied in the computational complexity (cs.CC) and logic in computer science (cs.LO) sub-categories. The use of and-or trees and circuits suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the problem of deciding the existence of succinct models can be seen as a combinatorial optimization problem, which is often studied in the discrete mathematics (cs.DM) sub-category.
